## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of comprehensive and unbiased sources. The case's complexity and the emotional nature of the debates may lead to polarized perspectives in the available literature. Additionally, the absence of a living will in Schiavo's case makes it difficult to generalize the findings to situations where such documentation exists. Further research could explore the long-term legislative changes prompted by the case and its impact on similar legal battles.

